jQuery

using JS to manipulate the DOM

to be able to use jQuery include it in your html: 
<script src="http://code.jquery.com/jquery-2.1.1.min.js"></script>


to get the list of jQuery methods, write: console.log($.fn)


chaining 
$('.caption-text')
  .text('Magic!')
  .css('background-color', 'orange');


  Responding to User input: 
  Using anonymous functions, Brian demonstrates how to capture input from the user. He creates a simple click event which shows an alert box in the browser. The click event is passed the function that should be called when the event fires // (http://codepen.io/btholt/pen/ujlEz)